{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/set(keepalive:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/SocketProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"set(keepalive:)","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"keepalive","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO14SocketProtocolPAAE3set9keepaliveySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO6SocketC","extendedModule":"GIO"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socket\/set(keepalive:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"keepalive","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This option is only functional on certain kinds of sockets. (Notably,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tcp"},{"type":"text","text":" sockets.)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The exact time between pings is system- and protocol-dependent, but will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"normally be at least two hours. Most commonly, you would set this flag"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on a server socket if you want to allow clients to remain idle for long"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"periods of time, but also want to ensure that connections are eventually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"garbage-collected if clients crash or become unreachable."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets or unsets the "},{"code":"SO_KEEPALIVE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag on the underlying socket. When","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this flag is set on a socket, the system will attempt to verify that the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"remote socket endpoint is still present if a sufficiently long period of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time passes with no data being exchanged. If the system is unable to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"verify the presence of the remote endpoint, it will automatically close"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the connection.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Socket"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socket","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It supports both the UNIX socket implementations and winsock2 on Windows.","type":"text"}],"title":"Socket","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Socket","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket/set(keepalive:)":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/